Plot.
The second and third novels in author Anne Rice's popular book series The 
Vampire Chronicles provide the inspiration for this horror sequel starring 
ill-fated actress and recording artist Aaliyah, who was killed in an 
airplane crash before the film's release. Stuart Townsend is the vampire 
Lestat, who has awakened from a century-long slumber and turned his 
considerable energy to rock music. His vampirism identity mistaken for 
a Gothic hard rock publicity stunt along the lines of Kiss or Marilyn 
Manson, he quickly becomes a pop music sensation. Lestat's powerful 
music reaches the ear of the slumbering Akasha (Aaliyah), the 
millennia-old "queen of the vampires" who was the first immortal 
bloodsucker. Akasha is soon free and embarking on a quest to seize 
control of the world with Lestat at her side. In the meantime, Lestat 
becomes an object of fascination for Jesse Reeves (Marguerite Moreau), 
member of a secret order studying the supernatural called the Talamasca, 
and a band of ancient vampires come together in an effort to stop Akasha, 
even though her destruction could potentially cause their own deaths. 
Queen of the Damned co-stars Lena Olin and Vincent Perez.
